00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:27,610
And so that's interesting
because what it really

1207
00:51:27,610 --> 00:51:28,910
points to is two things.

1208
00:51:28,910 --> 00:51:32,170
One the extent to which much
of our feelings of happiness

1209
00:51:32,170 --> 00:51:34,910
are relative, in particular,
relative to our peers.

1210
00:51:34,910 --> 00:51:37,570
So there's that
social aspect again.

1211
00:51:37,570 --> 00:51:40,660
And the fact that
most of the time, we

1212
00:51:40,660 --> 00:51:43,150
are not very good at
orienting ourselves

1213
00:51:43,150 --> 00:51:44,253
in the longer arc of time.

1214
00:51:44,253 --> 00:51:45,670
We're pretty good
at knowing where

1215
00:51:45,670 --> 00:51:47,712
we are in the arc of a
day, or the arc of a week,

1216
00:51:47,712 --> 00:51:50,680
or the arc of a month, or even
a year, but that most of us

1217
00:51:50,680 --> 00:51:52,510
are not very good at
reflecting on where

1218
00:51:52,510 --> 00:51:53,968
we are in our life arc.

