1462
01:02:33,060 --> 01:02:38,340
my read is that when people win
the lottery or acquire wealth

1463
01:02:38,340 --> 01:02:41,220
through inheritance, some
form of wealth acquisition

1464
01:02:41,220 --> 01:02:44,670
that is sudden and that wasn't
preceded by a specific effort

1465
01:02:44,670 --> 01:02:45,900
to gain that wealth, right.

1466
01:02:45,900 --> 01:02:48,330
Buying a lottery ticket
is a pretty quick thing.

1467
01:02:48,330 --> 01:02:50,640
Inheritance is something
that you simply

1468
01:02:50,640 --> 01:02:54,390
get by virtue of who you are,
not necessarily by effort.

1469
01:02:54,390 --> 01:02:59,460
Well, that led to increases
in self-reported happiness

1470
01:02:59,460 --> 01:03:02,430
compared to prior to the
inheritance of the lottery win,

1471
01:03:02,430 --> 01:03:04,800
but it wasn't as
substantial as you

1472
01:03:04,800 --> 01:03:07,440
might imagine if
you are approaching

1473
01:03:07,440 --> 01:03:09,900
the notion of
happiness simply from,

1474
01:03:09,900 --> 01:03:12,000
well, more money
equals more happiness.

1475
01:03:12,000 --> 01:03:16,290
And while it is true that people
who are rendered paraplegic

1476
01:03:16,290 --> 01:03:20,940
or who undergo psychological
traumas or physical traumas

1477
01:03:20,940 --> 01:03:25,690
of any various kind
are, and frankly,

1478
01:03:25,690 --> 01:03:28,200
are remarkably
resilient in many cases.

1479
01:03:28,200 --> 01:03:31,380
They can still manage to
go about life and work

1480
01:03:31,380 --> 01:03:33,870
and engage in
relationships, et cetera.

1481
01:03:33,870 --> 01:03:38,100
There is a visible decrease
in overall levels of happiness

1482
01:03:38,100 --> 01:03:40,470
and well-being,
in particular, if

1483
01:03:40,470 --> 01:03:42,690
the psychological
and physical trauma

1484
01:03:42,690 --> 01:03:47,580
renders their nervous system
different in a way that

1485
01:03:47,580 --> 01:03:51,810
impacts other major areas of
life and enjoyment for them.

1486
01:03:51,810 --> 01:03:54,850
And that's certainly true
one year out from the trauma.

1487
01:03:54,850 --> 01:03:57,118
So the point is that
we do need to reframe

1488
01:03:57,118 --> 01:03:59,160
this idea that whether or
not you win the lottery

1489
01:03:59,160 --> 01:04:01,463
or become paraplegic or
suffer some major trauma,

1490
01:04:01,463 --> 01:04:02,880
your levels of
happiness are going

1491
01:04:02,880 --> 01:04:05,130
to be the same three
months or a year later.

1492
01:04:05,130 --> 01:04:06,910
I don't think that's accurate.

1493
01:04:06,910 --> 01:04:09,510
And in fact, Dr. Dan
Gilbert emphasized

1494
01:04:09,510 --> 01:04:13,260
that that's not accurate
even in that initial study.

1495
01:04:13,260 --> 01:04:15,060
And I think it's
an important thing

1496
01:04:15,060 --> 01:04:17,730
to frame because that's
such a popular notion.

1497
01:04:17,730 --> 01:04:19,980
Or that that idea
combined with the idea

1498
01:04:19,980 --> 01:04:22,530
that increased earnings
don't make us happy

1499
01:04:22,530 --> 01:04:26,910
combined with the idea that
we are happy early in life

1500
01:04:26,910 --> 01:04:30,270
but then as more demands arise
in life, we become less happy,

1501
01:04:30,270 --> 01:04:31,770
and then we become happy again.

1502
01:04:31,770 --> 01:04:33,750
And that idea is
we already explored

1503
01:04:33,750 --> 01:04:34,785
is not necessarily true.

1504
01:04:34,785 --> 01:04:36,660
Frankly, I knew a lot
of teenagers and people

1505
01:04:36,660 --> 01:04:39,235
in their early 20s that
are pretty unhappy who

1506
01:04:39,235 --> 01:04:41,610
then become happier later as
