1577
01:07:45,432 --> 01:07:46,890
And as I mentioned
earlier, we have

1578
01:07:46,890 --> 01:07:49,680
this episode on dopamine
motivation and drive.

1579
01:07:49,680 --> 01:07:53,700
The notion of
synthetic happiness

1580
01:07:53,700 --> 01:07:56,760
is not simply about
imagining happiness,

1581
01:07:56,760 --> 01:07:59,310
or thinking about happiness
or anticipating happiness.

1582
01:07:59,310 --> 01:08:01,950
To some extent, it is,
but it relates to a number

1583
01:08:01,950 --> 01:08:03,330
of other important themes.

1584
01:08:03,330 --> 01:08:05,670
But it is grounded
very thoroughly

1585
01:08:05,670 --> 01:08:09,030
in the neurobiology
of dopamine rewards.

1586
01:08:09,030 --> 01:08:12,070
And I'll talk about some of that
neurobiology in a few moments.

1587
01:08:12,070 --> 01:08:14,700
But I want to take
a couple of minutes

1588
01:08:14,700 --> 01:08:16,920
and talk about what
synthetic happiness is

1589
01:08:16,920 --> 01:08:18,660
and what some of
the conditions are

1590
01:08:18,660 --> 01:08:20,729
for allowing us to
access the state

1591
01:08:20,729 --> 01:08:22,479
of so-called
synthetic happiness.

1592
01:08:22,479 --> 01:08:24,600
And I want to point
out at the outset

1593
01:08:24,600 --> 01:08:28,979
that synthetic happiness, while
it might sound synthetic A.K.A.

1594
01:08:28,979 --> 01:08:31,080
false, it's anything but.

1595
01:08:31,080 --> 01:08:33,990
It actually turns out to be
among the more and perhaps

1596
01:08:33,990 --> 01:08:35,850
the more potent
form of happiness

1597
01:08:35,850 --> 01:08:37,109
that we can all access.

1598
01:08:37,109 --> 01:08:41,069
And this is where themes
related to our control

1599
01:08:41,069 --> 01:08:43,170
over our own
internal state really

1600
01:08:43,170 --> 01:08:46,010
become not only valid
but very powerful.

1601
01:08:46,010 --> 01:08:50,380
So, for instance, Dr.
Dan Gilbert and others

1602
01:08:50,380 --> 01:08:55,420
have explored how opportunity
and choice, that is, freedom

1603
01:08:55,420 --> 01:08:57,729
can and can't lead to
states of happiness.

1604
01:08:57,729 --> 01:09:01,640
And the results of those studies
are very solid and, frankly,

1605
01:09:01,640 --> 01:09:02,950
very surprising.

1606
01:09:02,950 --> 01:09:05,830
Until you understand the
results, and once you do,

1607
01:09:05,830 --> 01:09:08,800
I think you will immediately
see areas of your own life

1608
01:09:08,800 --> 01:09:11,800
that you can start to
access more happiness, again

1609
01:09:11,800 --> 01:09:14,620
genuine happiness,
simply by framing

1610
01:09:14,620 --> 01:09:16,359
certain choices in
a particular way

1611
01:09:16,359 --> 01:09:18,729
and maybe even by
eliminating choices.

1612
01:09:18,729 --> 01:09:20,649
Now I'd like to focus
on the research aimed

1613
01:09:20,649 --> 01:09:24,250
at understanding what increases
our levels of happiness.

1614
01:09:24,250 --> 01:09:27,010
And I'd like to frame this
under the umbrella of two

1615
01:09:27,010 --> 01:09:27,830
major themes.

1616
01:09:27,830 --> 01:09:30,729
The first theme is
so-called natural happiness.

1617
01:09:30,729 --> 01:09:33,430
Natural happiness is the sort
of happiness that most of us

1618
01:09:33,430 --> 01:09:34,760
are familiar with.

1619
01:09:34,760 --> 01:09:36,700
So the kind of
happiness that we expect

1620
01:09:36,700 --> 01:09:40,479
to have if we, for
instance, complete a degree.

1621
01:09:40,479 --> 01:09:43,149
Hopefully, a degree in a topic
meaningful and interesting

1622
01:09:43,149 --> 01:09:45,430
to us but a degree nonetheless.

1623
01:09:45,430 --> 01:09:47,590
Or we find a mate.

1624
01:09:47,590 --> 01:09:49,990
Hopefully, a mate that we
enjoy spending time with.

1625
01:09:49,990 --> 01:09:53,020
Or, for instance, making a
certain income or finding

1626
01:09:53,020 --> 01:09:55,450
work that we enjoy
on a regular basis.

1627
01:09:55,450 --> 01:09:56,980
All of those are
forms of happiness

1628
01:09:56,980 --> 01:09:59,440
that, from a very early
time in development,

1629
01:09:59,440 --> 01:10:01,830
we are taught exist.

1630
01:10:01,830 --> 01:10:03,580
For instance, even
when we are very young,

1631
01:10:03,580 --> 01:10:05,230
we are told that our
birthday is coming

1632
01:10:05,230 --> 01:10:06,550
and that we are going
to get presents,

1633
01:10:06,550 --> 01:10:07,967
and those presents
are going to be

1634
01:10:07,967 --> 01:10:11,012
focused on knowledge of
things that we already enjoy.

1635
01:10:11,012 --> 01:10:12,970
So if you're a little
kid, and you like trucks,

1636
01:10:12,970 --> 01:10:15,100
or you're a little kid
and you like dolls,

1637
01:10:15,100 --> 01:10:17,920
you can sort of expect that
those gifts will bring you

1638
01:10:17,920 --> 01:10:19,690
some level of joy or happiness.

1639
01:10:19,690 --> 01:10:22,540
And while that's a
small child example,

1640
01:10:22,540 --> 01:10:24,850
that general notion
of natural happiness

1641
01:10:24,850 --> 01:10:28,960
is, of course, one that
persists into adolescence,

1642
01:10:28,960 --> 01:10:31,580
into young adulthood,
and into adulthood.

1643
01:10:31,580 --> 01:10:35,020
And we quite understandably
come to associate

1644
01:10:35,020 --> 01:10:39,280
this feeling of joy or happiness
with the receiving of things

1645
01:10:39,280 --> 01:10:41,830
or the acquisition of
things, whether by effort,

1646
01:10:41,830 --> 01:10:44,390
by gift, by inheritance,
or some other form.

1647
01:10:44,390 --> 01:10:45,680
So that's natural happiness.

1648
01:10:45,680 --> 01:10:48,520
And yet, as I mentioned
a little bit earlier,

1649
01:10:48,520 --> 01:10:51,250
there's also this notion
of synthetic happiness.

1650
01:10:51,250 --> 01:10:53,800
And some of the more interesting
and exciting research

1651
01:10:53,800 --> 01:10:56,470
in the fields of psychology
and, in fact, neuroscience

1652
01:10:56,470 --> 01:10:59,800
point to this idea of
synthetic happiness

1653
01:10:59,800 --> 01:11:03,700
as at least as powerful
a source of happiness

1654
01:11:03,700 --> 01:11:05,380
as natural happiness.

1655
01:11:05,380 --> 01:11:09,250
Again, at least as powerful
and perhaps even more powerful.

1656
01:11:09,250 --> 01:11:12,340
And of course, one has to take a
slightly different view of what

1657
01:11:12,340 --> 01:11:15,430
happiness is in order to accept
this idea that we can create

1658
01:11:15,430 --> 01:11:19,090
