1882
01:20:45,670 --> 01:20:46,712
No pictures on the walls.

1883
01:20:46,712 --> 01:20:48,460
Other people
benefit tremendously

1884
01:20:48,460 --> 01:20:51,800
from having photos or plants
in their environment and so on.

1885
01:20:51,800 --> 01:20:54,160
You really have to determine
what's needed for you

1886
01:20:54,160 --> 01:20:55,552
and do your best
to try and place

1887
01:20:55,552 --> 01:20:57,010
those things into
your environment,

1888
01:20:57,010 --> 01:20:59,260
or rather, place yourself
into an environment that

1889
01:20:59,260 --> 01:21:02,420
is conducive to you
synthesizing your happiness.

1890
01:21:02,420 --> 01:21:04,180
In fact, the
powerful interaction

1891
01:21:04,180 --> 01:21:06,820
between our environment
and our own ability

1892
01:21:06,820 --> 01:21:09,850
to generate certain
kinds of emotions

1893
01:21:09,850 --> 01:21:11,810
is well established
not just for happiness

1894
01:21:11,810 --> 01:21:13,060
but for things like gratitude.

1895
01:21:13,060 --> 01:21:16,450
So, for instance, there's a
classic study from AMES A-M-E-S

1896
01:21:16,450 --> 01:21:20,590
in 2004 that was
focused on gratitude.

1897
01:21:20,590 --> 01:21:23,230
And we've had an episode
on gratitude before.

1898
01:21:23,230 --> 01:21:24,820
The basic takeaway
of that episode

1899
01:21:24,820 --> 01:21:28,270
is that it turns out
receiving gratitude

1900
01:21:28,270 --> 01:21:33,010
is a more powerful
stimulus for the release

1901
01:21:33,010 --> 01:21:35,680
of neurochemicals and activation
