1902
01:21:35,680 --> 01:21:37,240
with so-called
prosocial behaviors

1903
01:21:37,240 --> 01:21:40,300
and feelings of well-being,
including happiness.

1904
01:21:40,300 --> 01:21:44,860
But also observing stories in
the form of movies or books

1905
01:21:44,860 --> 01:21:47,140
or other narratives of
other people receiving help

1906
01:21:47,140 --> 01:21:49,570
is also a very powerful
stimulus for gratitude.

1907
01:21:49,570 --> 01:21:52,930
Also, giving gratitude
is very powerful but not

1908
01:21:52,930 --> 01:21:55,060
as powerful as receiving
gratitude, at least

1909
01:21:55,060 --> 01:21:57,010
that's what the research
says, or observing

1910
01:21:57,010 --> 01:22:00,370
powerful exchanges of gratitude
between other individuals.

1911
01:22:00,370 --> 01:22:02,260
What the study
from AMES showed is

1912
01:22:02,260 --> 01:22:06,550
that gratitude as a state
of mind and as an emotion

1913
01:22:06,550 --> 01:22:08,390
does not exist in a vacuum.

1914
01:22:08,390 --> 01:22:11,602
It's not independent
of our surroundings.

1915
01:22:11,602 --> 01:22:13,060
So, for instance,
just writing down

1916
01:22:13,060 --> 01:22:14,852
all the things you're
grateful for while it

1917
01:22:14,852 --> 01:22:17,440
has some positive impact,
the impact of that

1918
01:22:17,440 --> 01:22:19,960
or receiving gratitude
or observing gratitude

1919
01:22:19,960 --> 01:22:22,420
is far more potent, right.

1920
01:22:22,420 --> 01:22:24,940
Bigger increases in
happiness and feelings

1921
01:22:24,940 --> 01:22:27,190
of well-being and indeed
neurochemicals and activation

1922
01:22:27,190 --> 01:22:30,160
of brain areas associated
with happiness and well-being

1923
01:22:30,160 --> 01:22:32,020
when there's a reciprocity.

1924
01:22:32,020 --> 01:22:35,147
When the person receiving
understands something

1925
01:22:35,147 --> 01:22:36,730
about the person
that's giving to them

1926
01:22:36,730 --> 01:22:38,897
and understands that the
person is giving genuinely,

1927
01:22:38,897 --> 01:22:39,439
for instance.

1928
01:22:39,439 --> 01:22:41,105
So there's an
environmental interaction.

1929
01:22:41,105 --> 01:22:42,700
It's not just about
receiving, it's

1930
01:22:42,700 --> 01:22:46,210
receiving from somebody that you
know genuinely wants to give.

1931
01:22:46,210 --> 01:22:49,450
And likewise, for the
giver in that equation,

1932
01:22:49,450 --> 01:22:51,970
the feelings of
well-being are far greater

1933
01:22:51,970 --> 01:22:54,550
when the person
receiving whatever

1934
01:22:54,550 --> 01:22:58,390
it is money, food, assistance
in some form or another.

1935
01:22:58,390 --> 01:23:00,970
Could be physical
assistance, et cetera.

1936
01:23:00,970 --> 01:23:04,030
When the giver has knowledge
that the person receiving it

1937
01:23:04,030 --> 01:23:06,187
genuinely needed the thing
that they are receiving.

1938
01:23:06,187 --> 01:23:08,770
So the important finding within
the research, again and again,

1939
01:23:08,770 --> 01:23:12,020
is that happiness doesn't
exist in a vacuum.

